File: src/auth/login.js
Line: 26–29
Severity: Critical
Issue: JWT is signed without an `expiresIn` option, so issued tokens never expire and cannot be invalidated by rotation.
Fix: Add expiry: `jwt.sign({ ... }, jwtSecret, { expiresIn: '1h' })`
File: src/middleware/authMiddleware.js
Line: 14–15
Severity: Critical
Issue: JWT verification failure calls `next()` instead of returning 401 — every request with an invalid or expired token bypasses authentication and proceeds as if authenticated.
Fix: Replace `next()` in the error branch with `return res.status(401).json({ error: 'Invalid or expired token' });`

