File: src/db/connection.js
Line: 10
Severity: Critical
Issue: Database password is hardcoded as a string literal — any developer with repo access or a leaked build artifact gets the credential.
Fix: Replace with `password: process.env.DB_PASSWORD` and remove the literal value.

File: src/db/connection.js
Line: 3–11
Severity: Major
Issue: Pool is initialized without `max`, `idleTimeoutMillis`, or `connectionTimeoutMillis` — under load the pool will exhaust available connections with no timeout safety, and connection hangs will block indefinitely.
Fix: Add pool limits:
```js
const pool = new Pool({
  ...
  max: 10,
  idleTimeoutMillis: 30000,
  connectionTimeoutMillis: 2000,
});
```

File: src/db/connection.js
Line: 13
Severity: Major
Issue: No `pool.on('error')` handler — an idle client error event (e.g. unexpected disconnect) is unhandled and will crash the Node.js process.
Fix: Add `pool.on('error', (err) => { console.error('Unexpected pool error', err); });` after pool construction.
