```
File: src/jobs/cleanupJob.js
Line: 7–17
Severity: Major
Issue: Read-then-delete across two separate queries with no transaction — sessions expiring between the SELECT and DELETE can cause inconsistent state, and sessions inserted after the SELECT but before the DELETE will not be cleaned up correctly.
Fix: Wrap both queries in a transaction, or collapse to a single atomic query: `DELETE FROM sessions WHERE expires_at < NOW() RETURNING session_id`.

File: src/jobs/cleanupJob.js
Line: 21–25
Severity: Major
Issue: The `.catch()` handler only logs `err.message` and swallows the error — cleanup failures are silently ignored, so degraded state (sessions never cleaned, pool exhaustion, DB outage) is invisible to any alerting or process supervisor.
Fix: Re-throw after logging, or emit a metric/alert: `console.error(...); throw err;` — or at minimum preserve the full error object (`err`) rather than just `err.message`.
File: src/utils/pagination.js
