Issue: `paginatedQuery` is async but has no try/catch — if either `pool.query()` call throws (connection error, bad query, etc.), the rejected promise propagates uncaught to the caller.
Fix: Wrap the function body in a try/catch, or ensure every call site wraps it; at minimum the function itself should catch and rethrow with context so the caller can distinguish DB errors from logic errors.
